The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest on July 17, 2012. The press gaggle took place aboard Air Force One en route to San Antonio, Texas. Earnest answered questions about various topics including health insurance for seasonal workers, Mitt Romney's taxes, the fiscal cliff, the situation in Syria, the Federal Reserve, the President's campaign schedule, and the President being on the Kiss Cam at a basketball game. Earnest also mentioned an ad in Pennsylvania questioning whether Romney paid his fair share in taxes and highlighted the President's differing vision for the country.